            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EPaul%20was%20determined%20never%20to%20yield%20to%20anything%20opposed%20to%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20Gospel.%20He%20wrote%20to%20the%20Ephesians%2C%20%22Do%20not%20give%20the%20devil%20a%20foothold%22%20(Ephesians%204%3A27%20NIV).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20duty%20of%20the%20Christian%20parent%2C%20pastor%2C%20or%20leader%20is%20to%20%22be%20careful!%20Watch%20out%20for%20attacks%20from%20the%20Devil%2C%20your%20great%20enemy.%20He%20prowls%20around%20like%20a%20roaring%20lion%2C%20looking%20for%20some%20victim%20to%20devour%22%20(1%20Peter%205%3A8).%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Lord%20warned%20Isaiah%20about%20the%20need%20for%20alertness%2C%20saying%2C%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22Put%20a%20watchman%20on%20the%20city%20wall%20to%20shout%20out%20what%20he%20sees.%20Tell%20him%20to%20sound%20the%20alert%20when%20he%20sees%20chariots%20drawn%20by%20horses%20and%20warriors%20mounted%20on%20donkeys%20and%20camels%22%20(Isaiah%2021%3A6-7).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESatan%20seeks%20to%20weasel%20his%20way%20into%20our%20churches%20and%20families%20through%20our%20slack%20oversight%2C%20our%20tolerance%20of%20his%20encroachment%2C%20and%20our%20yielding%20to%20his%20advances.%20Even%20when%20the%20great%20apostle%20Peter%20was%20being%20swayed%20by%20the%20hypocrisy%20of%20the%20Judaizers%2C%20Paul%20stood%20boldly%20against%20him%2C%20saying%2C%20%22I%20had%20to%20oppose%20him%20publicly%2C%20speaking%20strongly%20against%20what%20he%20was%20doing%2C%20for%20it%20was%20very%20wrong%22%20(Galatians%202%3A11).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20enemy%20hates%20your%20liberty%20in%20Christ%20and%20does%20his%20best%20to%20put%20you%20back%20under%20the%20%22yoke%20of%20bondage%22%20(Galatians%205%3A1%20KJV).%20Don't%20give%20in%20to%20anything%20that%20is%20not%20in%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20Gospel.%20Stand%20your%20ground%20against%20the%20devil%2C%20and%20%22he%20will%20flee%20from%20you%22%20(James%204%3A7).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
